@NODE introduction "cnmp/--introduction--"


                               Introduction
                               ============
   Because of the countless hours or work I have put into this project,
I DO expect every programmer/developer/Sysop who uses CNMP when coding
to REGISTER IT.  Great care has been taken to assure that the documentation
is as clear and concise as possible and that the package is VERY stable
provided you READ the documentation.

   You don't need to worry about reading C= Amiga ROM Kernal Manuals for the
Messaging system because CNMP takes most of that burden.  What you need to
know is spelled out pretty clearly and I am available on a few networks
(including FidoNet and Clink) to aid you in times of utter disaster or when
something just doesn't go "click".  The registration fee(s), as with most of
my other projects, are very liberal and I'm not asking to make millions but
I DO expect support if support is to be gained in return.  The Amiga
community as a whole needs to embrace it's own more than ever in these times
and I plan to stick it out no matter what comes of Escom and it's plans for
us.  As long as there is an Amiga computer left on the face of the earth, and
provided my own doesn't go schizoid on me, I will be here to support them.
Make no mistake about that. BUT there is a price - I need to eat. :)

   Please support developers as they (we?) are the Amiga's lifeblood.
Anyways, back to a lighter note and the reason you grabbed this
package -> CNetMultiPort!

@ENDNODE
